<DOC><DOCNO> AP900726-0240 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-07-26-90 1147EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r f BC-Earns-Blackandamp;Decker     07-26 0182</FIRST><SECOND>BC-Earns-Black andamp; Decker,0188</SECOND><HEAD>Posts Profit for Second-Quarter</HEAD><DATELINE>TOWSON, Md. (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   The Black andamp; Decker Corp. said Thursday itposted a profit of $16.1 million in the second quarter after losing$5.2 million in the same period a year ago as its revenue soared 44percent.   The maker of power tools and other products used commerciallyand around the house said its profit amouynted to 26 cents a sharein the three months ended July 1 in contrast to a loss of ninecents per share a year earlier.   Revenue climbed to $1.22 billion from $847.6 million a yearearlier.   The results include revenues and earnings of Information andElectronic Systems and Dynapert, formerly reported on theconsolidated balance sheet as businesses held for sale. Thecompanies contributed approximately $220 million in revenue duringthe quarter.   For the firtst half, the company said it earned $26.1 million,or 43 cents a share, up 23 percent from $20.7 million, or 35 centsa share, a year earlier.   Revenue for the first half rose 45 percent to $2.05 billion from$1.42 billion.</TEXT></DOC>